    <item>
      <title>Result Class - Components</title>
      <link>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/resultclass-components/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/resultclass-components/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h4 id=&#34;disclaimer-image-is-generated-using-chatgpt&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DISCLAIMER:&lt;/strong&gt; Image is generated using &lt;code&gt;ChatGPT&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/h4&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For my upcoming book on &lt;code&gt;DBIx::Class&lt;/code&gt;, I have been working on examples to support the thoeretical chapters. This exercise helped me fill several gaps in my narration. I started with &lt;a href=&#34;https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/dbic-resultset&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DBIx::Class - Result Class &amp;amp; ResultSet Class&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt; followed by a three-part series on &lt;code&gt;Schema Class&lt;/code&gt;:  &lt;a href=&#34;https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/dbic-schema&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 1&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;,   &lt;a href=&#34;https://theweeklychallenge.org/dbic-schema-part-2&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 2&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;  and &lt;a href=&#34;https://theweeklychallenge.org/blog/dbic-schema-part-3&#34;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In this post, I am going to explore the power of &lt;code&gt;Components&lt;/code&gt; within &lt;code&gt;Result&lt;/code&gt; class. This will likely be another multi-part series, as components make it easy to get the job done with minimal effort.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
